
Overview of noun simplicity

The noun simplicity has 5 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (4) simplicity, simpleness -- (the quality of being simple or uncompounded; "the simplicity of a crystal")
2. (1) simplicity, simpleness, simple mindedness -- (a lack of penetration or subtlety; "they took advantage of her simplicity")
3. simplicity, simmpleness -- (absence of affectation or pretense)
4. ease, easiness, simplicity, simpleness -- (freedom from difficulty or hardship or effort; "he rose through the ranks with apparent ease"; "they put it into containers for ease of transportation"; "the very easiness of the deed held her back")
5. chasteness, restraint, simplicity, simpleness -- (lack of ornamentation; "the room was simply decorated with great restraint")
